flowchart TD
    REG[Validated registry contract]
    SRC[Declared source fingerprints]
    CFG[Configuration fingerprint]
    REN[Renderer identifier / interface / semantic version]
    TGT[Current target and partition fingerprints]
    SEM[Target semantics]
    ACC[Acceptance state]
    GSET[Required gate-set identity]
    BASE[Base / ref context]

    EVAL[Lifecycle-owned freshness evaluation]
    CLASS[Freshness classification: fresh / stale / invalid / indeterminate]
    FIND[Structured independent findings and subreasons]
    TRUST[Existing DPA-100 consumer trust state]
    GATE{Existing gate authority}

    PASS[pass]
    WARNING[warning]
    FAILURE[failure / fail closed]
    ACCEPT[Record acceptance state and become accepted]
    PRESERVE[Preserve bytes and prior state]
    ABANDON[Abandon attempt when lifecycle attempt cannot complete]

    REG --> EVAL
    SRC --> EVAL
    CFG --> EVAL
    REN --> EVAL
    TGT --> EVAL
    SEM --> EVAL
    ACC --> EVAL
    GSET --> EVAL
    BASE --> EVAL

    EVAL --> CLASS
    EVAL --> FIND
    CLASS --> GATE
    FIND --> GATE
    TRUST --> GATE

    GATE -->|all mandatory checks pass| PASS
    GATE -->|only staged non-blocking findings| WARNING
    GATE -->|freshness, safety or evaluation failure| FAILURE

    PASS --> ACCEPT
    WARNING --> PRESERVE
    FAILURE --> PRESERVE
    FAILURE --> ABANDON

    NOTE1[Freshness classification does not replace consumer trust state]
    NOTE2[observe / warn / block-new / strict are policy stages, not gate outcomes]
    NOTE3[Renderer never assigns findings, trust state, gate decision or acceptance]
    NOTE1 -. classification boundary .-> CLASS
    NOTE2 -. policy boundary .-> GATE
    NOTE3 -. authority boundary .-> EVAL